tldr: The agent evaluated the codebase for a sleep questionnaire application
  against an SOW, identifying missing database, dashboard, and authentication
  features. It then implemented a PostgreSQL database for questionnaire
  responses, a simple password-protected admin dashboard with CSV export, and
  updated the questionnaire form to save data.
overview: The user initiated a project to implement database storage and an
  admin dashboard for a "Sleep Questionnaire Application" based on a provided
  Statement of Work. The agent first assessed the existing codebase, identifying
  the lack of a database for questionnaire responses, a data retrieval mechanism
  (like CSV export), an admin dashboard, and an authentication system. After
  clarifying the desired authentication complexity (simple password) and the
  specific demographic data to be collected, the agent proceeded with the
  implementation. This involved updating the application's data types and
  validation schemas, creating a new Prisma model for  in
  a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), and developing API endpoints for saving,
  retrieving, and exporting questionnaire data as CSV. A lightweight,
  cookie-based authentication system was built to protect the new admin routes.
  Finally, a functional admin dashboard with a login page, a table view of
  responses, and a CSV download feature was created, and the main questionnaire
  form was modified to submit data to the new database. All tasks were completed
  as specified in the plan.
